gaiting
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:  1
Definition:[used earlier elsewhere, but sp. in New Zealand for flax drying] the forming of gaits, stacks or wigwams of flax fibres to enhance drying in drying paddocks.


Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain: Rural
Region: [none]
