Citations
Date:  0/0/1976
Source:  From the Beginning: chronicles of a county
Author:  KERR
Vol / Page:  292
Edition:
Quote:  Out of the tanks, a machine feeds the retted straw...on to the drying paddocks. There it half-dries, when it is ready for 'gaiting,' the wet underside becoming the outside of the 'gait.' They are these small wigwams one sees in rows in the drying fields, and are another stage of drying.
